org.team1540.rooster.testers.motor

Class BurnoutTester

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.team1540.rooster.testers.AbstractTester<IMotorController,Boolean>
      • org.team1540.rooster.testers.motor.BurnoutTester
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sendable, Runnable, Tester<IMotorController,Boolean>

    public class BurnoutTester
extends AbstractTester<IMotorController,Boolean>
implements Sendable
    Reports motor burnouts by comparing the current draw across a series of similarly-purposed motors and reporting low outliers or checking if a single motor is below the cutoff.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      BurnoutTester(IMotorController... motorsToTest)
      Construct a new instance with the default logTime of 150 seconds and an update delay of 500 ms, using the testBurnoutMultiMotor(IMotorController) if there is more than one motor and testBurnoutSingleMotor(IMotorController) if there is one or few motors.
      BurnoutTester(List<IMotorController> motorsToTest)
      Construct a new instance with the default logTime of 150 seconds and an update delay of 500 ms, using the testBurnoutMultiMotor(IMotorController) if there are more than two motor sand testBurnoutSingleMotor(IMotorController) if there two two or few motors.
